This song is one of the greatest and my favorite song of the 2020's, because of its revival of 80's synth pop combined with some pop rock elements. I'm a synthesizer and 80's guy myself, and I've heard multiple synth pop bands, and I can hear striking similarities to Tears for Fears and a-ha, both being pop rock and synth pop bands. I can compare this song with "Everybody Wants To Rule The World" because they sound a little similar. I feel like End of Beginning is so well-composed, well-structured, and well-written in every way, that I just want to listen to it as many as I want, because it just sounds *_too good._* Everyone has their own interpretations of this song, either a final sendoff to 2024 (primarily because of the lyric, "Remember '24?"), or a nostalgic feeling. For me, I would go something like one of the usuals, a nostalgic feeling, like looking back to your childhood years.

This song is a bit like "Africa" by Toto, "Don't Stop Believin'" by Journey, and "Carry On My Wayward Son" all rolled into one, but this one may be my favorite of all of those great songs. This just...hits different. And boy, does it hit hard. It makes me inexplicably sad, and it also makes me want to jam. It makes me nostalgic for a place I didn't grow up in and long for something I'm not sure I ever had. And my God, those harmonies melt me like butter on a hot summer day. Those harmonies are out of thus world, they're so good. And EVERTHING in the song--the lyrics, the synth, and the drums, just to name a few--compliment them so f*cking well. Listening to this almost makes me want to cry.
